⭐ Short Announcement: How Copyright Works
Copyright protection is automatic the moment you create something.  
You don’t need to file anything, register anything, or publish anything for your work to be protected. As soon as you create an original piece of content — art, writing, music, design, code, or any creative expression — it is automatically covered under copyright law.

Copyright gives you the exclusive right to:

reproduce your work

distribute your work

display your work

create adaptations or derivatives

This protection applies worldwide under international agreements.

However, while copyright is automatic, proving authorship and timeline can be difficult without clear evidence. That’s why creators use the IP Continuity Watermark Standard and the public vault — to create a visible, timestamped record that strengthens their ability to show when their work existed and that they are the original creator.

Copyright protects your rights.
Continuity helps you prove them.
